Ё  Video:                                                                     Ё
Ё   - 1080i/p sources are to be cropped and resized using sharp resizers such Ё
Ё     as  Lanczos/Lanczos4,  Spline36,   or   Blackman.  Bicubic  is  banned. Ё
Ё   - Video  taken  from  the  decoded  HD  output  of  a  set-top box  (e.g. Ё
Ё     component,  DVI,  HDMI)  may be used as a source; source must be tagged Ё
Ё     in  dirname as AHDTV. Releases taken from a natively recorded transport Ё
Ё     stream  shall  be  tagged as HDTV and do not dupe AHDTV releases. AHDTV Ё
Ё     releases do dupe HDTV. AHDTV captures must be done at the native format Ё
Ё     of the channel, i.e. 720p or 1080i.                                     Ё
Ё   - Improper  methods  of  IVTC  that  result  in  loss  of half the fields Ё
Ё     (SeparateFields.SelectEven,  YV12InterlacedSelectTopFields)  are banned Ё
Ё   - Improper  IVTC  methods  that  result  in jerky playback, such as Force Ё
Ё     Film, are banned                                                        Ё
Ё   - 1080i video sources must be deinterlaced with a smart deinterlacer such Ё
Ё     as Yadif. FieldDeinterlace is banned.                                   Ё
Ё   - Group  watermarks  of  any  kind  on  the  video  will not be tolerated Ё
Ё   - Intros,  outros,  betweenos,  or  any  other  form of defacement of the Ё
Ё     episode will not be tolerated                                           Ё
Ё   - Sources  that  sideconvert  1080i  to 720p (such as Bell Expressvu) are Ё
Ё     banned                                                                  Ё
Ё   - Upconverted  sources must not be done as 720p.x264. See notes regarding Ё
Ё     HR.PDTV.x264.                                                           Ё
Ё   - "Native" refers to the standard in which the video was produced (e.g.   Ё
Ё     NTSC or PAL). NTSC produced video is native to NTSC, PAL produced video Ё
Ё     is native to PAL. PAL produced video that is broadcast in NTSC is       Ё
Ё     converted. NTSC produced video that is broadcast in PAL is converted.   Ё
Ё   - Converted video that cannot be reversed to native must use CONVERT tag. Ё
Ё   - Converts dupe natives. Natives do not dupe converts.                    Ё
Ё                                                                             Ё
Ё  Audio:                                                                     Ё
Ё   - Must be original source audio, AC3 if available                         Ё
Ё   - Re-encoding/transcoding audio or faking header is forbidden             Ё
Ё   - Dupes  based  on audio format are forbidden and must be tagged INTERNAL Ё
Ё   - Multi-language audio tracks are not allowed.                            Ё
Ё   - Severe   audio   drops   resulting  in  a missing word or otherwise the Ё
Ё     inability  to   understand  material  dialogue  is  considered  to  be  Ё
Ё     technically flawed and may be propered.                                 Ё
Ё   - Audio  that  is  120ms  or  more  out of sync or drifts more than 120ms Ё
Ё     between any two points (e.g. needing -80 at one and +40 at another)  is Ё
Ё     considered   to   be   technically   flawed   and   may   be   propered Ё
Ё                                                                             Ё
Ё  Framerate:                                                                 Ё
Ё   - IVTC or deinterlacing must be applied as needed                         Ё
Ё   - 50/60fps  video  such as live events may be kept at original fps, if it Ё
Ё     was produced at such high rate (i.e. has unique frames)                 Ё
Ё   - In rare cases, 25/50Hz sources should be IVTC'd to 24fps.               Ё
Ё   - In rare cases, 30/60Hz sources should be IVTC'd to 25fps.               Ё
Ё     Failure to IVTC is a technical flaw.                                    Ё
Ё                                                                             Ё
